abstract: In 2016, a mysterious syndicate tried to steal $951 million from Bangladesh’s central bank - and laid bare a profound weakness in the system by which money moves around the world.

abstract: “Prelude,” two weeks of programming starting Tuesday, offers a taste of what the Shed has in store — about a year before it opens.
snippet: “Prelude,” two weeks of programming starting Tuesday, offers a taste of what the Shed has in store — about a year before it opens.
lead_paragraph: The Shed, the new cross-disciplinary arts center planned for the Far West Side of Manhattan, is still a hard-hat construction site, with an opening date of next spring. But starting on Tuesday, its creators will serve up two free weeks of arts events as an amuse-bouche, hoping to entice New Yorkers with an early look at the type of ambitious programming the Shed will eventually offer.

abstract: There are a lot of lawyers in New York, but few like Jim Walden, who has managed to be a part of some of the biggest political dramas in recent years.
snippet: There are a lot of lawyers in New York, but few like Jim Walden, who has managed to be a part of some of the biggest political dramas in recent years.
lead_paragraph: Two months into his first term as mayor, Bill de Blasio offered resounding praise for the lawyer he worked with during his campaign to oppose the closing of a cherished Brooklyn hospital.
